    "Beyond dropout (P_drop = 0.1), the Transformer uses label smoothing with epsilon_ls = 0.1 as an additional regularization technique. No other explicit regularization such as weight decay is mentioned.",
    "The Transformer Big established a new state-of-the-art BLEU score of 41.0 on WMT 2014 English-to-French, outperforming all previously published single models, including all previously published ensembles.",
    "Each sub-layer in the encoder — both the multi-head self-attention and the feed-forward network — has an input and output dimension of d_model = 512. This fixed dimensionality throughout the model facilitates the use of residual connections.",
    "The Transformer is the first transduction model relying entirely on self-attention to compute representations of its input and output without using sequence-aligned RNNs or convolution, representing a fundamental architectural departure.",
    "When the sequence length n exceeds the representation dimensionality d, self-attention layers are slower than recurrent layers because self-attention has O(n^2 * d) complexity versus O(n * d^2) for recurrence.",
    "For very long sequences, self-attention could be restricted to consider only a neighborhood of size r in the input sequence, which would increase the maximum path length to O(n/r) but reduce computational complexity.",
