    "The learning rate schedule is: lrate = d_model^(-0.5) * min(step_num^(-0.5), step_num * warmup_steps^(-1.5)). This increases the rate linearly for the first warmup_steps training steps, and decreases it thereafter proportionally to the inverse square root of the step number.",
    "The authors compared sinusoidal positional encodings with learned positional embeddings and found nearly identical results (within 0.1 BLEU), choosing sinusoidal encodings because they may allow the model to extrapolate to sequence lengths longer than those encountered during training.",
